name: basicsr
summary: open source image and video super-resolution toolbox
documentation_summary: BasicSR is an open-source toolbox for image and video restoration, including super-resolution, denoising, deblurring, and removing JPEG artifacts, based on PyTorch. It is available on PyPI as version 1.4.2, released on August 30, 2022. The project, licensed under the Apache License 2.0, is developed by Xintao Wang and aims to provide a comprehensive solution for enhancing image and video quality. BasicSR supports various programming languages, including Python versions 3, 3.7, and 3.8, and is OS-independent. The toolbox has been updated with new features like plot scripts, ECBSR training, and testing codes, and it integrates with projects like Real-ESRGAN and GFPGAN for practical image and face restoration.
